                     +------------------------------+
                     | N2Nv3 Protocol Specification !
                     +------------------------------+

Procedure
---------

Note: For details on the SN_HEADER see FORMATS section

1. Joining the Network

Joining the Network is done by a 4-way handshake with the supernode. The first
two packets are used for a DH Exchange, the second two to exchange information.

A -> S: handshake syn
S -> A: handshake syn-ack
A -> S: payload packet: SN_HEADER(supernode_register:),
                        A_MAC,A_N2N_IP, A_LOCAL_SOCK
S -> A: payload packet: SN_HEADER(supernode_register:ACK), A_PUB_SOCK

2. Supernode keep-alive

A -> S: payload packet: SN_HEADER(keep_alive:)
S -> A: payload packet: SN_HEADER(keep_alive:ACK)

3. ARP requests

A -> S: payload packet: SN_HEADER(address_resolution:),    B_IP
S -> A: payload packet: SN_HEADER(address_resolution:ACK), B_IP, B_MAC

4. Establishing p2p connection to another edge

A -> S: payload packet: SN_HEADER(edge_connect:), B_MAC,
                        A_Timeout, A_PUB_SOCK, A_LOCAL_SOCK
S -> B: payload packet: SN_HEADER(edge_connect:), B_MAC,
                        A_Timeout, A_PUB_SOCK, A_LOCAL_SOCK
B -> A: holepunch packet (will usually get lost)
B -> S: payload packet: SN_HEADER(edge_connect:ACK), A_MAC,
                        B_Timeout, B_PUB_SOCK, B_LOCAL_SOCK
S -> A: payload packet: SN_HEADER(edge_connect:ACK), A_MAC,
                        B_Timeout, B_PUB_SOCK, B_LOCAL_SOCK

A -> B: handshake syn
B -> A: handshake syn-ack
(final acknowledgement?)

5. Resume established connections with timeout for p2p hole

A -> S: payload packet: SN_HEADER(edge_resume:), B_MAC,
                A_Timeout, A_PUB_SOCK, A_LOCAL_SOCK
S -> B: payload packet: SN_HEADER(edge_resume:), B_MAC,
                A_Timeout, A_PUB_SOCK, A_LOCAL_SOCK
B -> A: holepunch packet
(alternatively use end-to-end key here?)

6. Data packets:

A -> B: payload packet: DATA

7. Rekeying:
?

DECODING
--------

Edge:
1. Read first four byte to Integer SPI
SPI == NULL:
  Parse header, check version
  switch(packet type)
    handshake syn:
      community name check ?
      HMAC check
      allocate new peer, save SPI
      DH
      send handshake syn-ack
    handshake syn-ack:
      HMAC check
      find_peer_by_spi (else: discard)
      DH (generate key)
    holepunch packet:
      discard
      
SPI != NULL:
  find peer P associated with SPI
      else discard
  check (throw away if bad) & decrypt payload to PL
  if SPI == supernode:
    decode SN_HEADER
    ... (TODO)
  if SPI != SUPERNODE:
    assemble ethernet frame
    put payload PL

Supernode:
1. Read first four byte to Integer SPI
SPI == NULL:
  Parse header, check version
  ... (TODO)
SPI != NULL:
  find peer P associated with SPI
      else discard
  check (throw away if bad) & decrypt payload to PL
  decode SN_HEADER
  ... (TODO)

FORMATS (work in progress)
-------

HEADER:

The header is sent for all non-payload packets after 4 ZERO-bytes

      0 1 2 3 4 5 6 7 0 1 2 3 4 5 6 7 0 1 2 3 4 5 6 7 0 1 2 3 4 5 6 7
     +---------------+---------------+---------------+---------------+
   0 ! Version       ! Crypt-Version ! Packet Type   ! Flags         !
     +---------------+---------------+---------------+---------------+

Packet Types: handshake, holepunch
Flags: ACK (acknowledge)

SN_HEADER:

the SN header is sent for all payload packets going to or coming from the
supernode

      0 1 2 3 4 5 6 7 0 1 2 3 4 5 6 7 0 1 2 3 4 5 6 7 0 1 2 3 4 5 6 7
     +---------------+---------------+---------------+---------------+
   0 ! Version       ! Crypt-Version ! Packet Type   ! Flags         !
     +---------------+---------------+---------------+---------------+

Packet Types: supernode_register, keep_alive, address_resolution,
	      edge_connect, edge_resume
Flags: ACK (acknowledge)



--------------------

SN_Flag = DH_INIT

      0 1 2 3 4 5 6 7 0 1 2 3 4 5 6 7 0 1 2 3 4 5 6 7 0 1 2 3 4 5 6 7
     +---------------+---------------+---------------+---------------+
   4 ! HMAC_IV + DH Values (ECDH or g, p, A) + KDF_SALT_A + HMAC
     +---------------+---------------+---------------+---------------+

SN_Flag = DH_INIT + ACK

      0 1 2 3 4 5 6 7 0 1 2 3 4 5 6 7 0 1 2 3 4 5 6 7 0 1 2 3 4 5 6 7
     +---------------+---------------+---------------+---------------+
   4 ! HMAC_IV + DH Values (ECDH or B) + KDF_SALT_S + HMAC
     +---------------+---------------+---------------+---------------+

If the DH_INIT flag is not set, the rest of the packet (payload) will be in a
cryptographic container of the following format:

      0 1 2 3 4 5 6 7 0 1 2 3 4 5 6 7 0 1 2 3 4 5 6 7 0 1 2 3 4 5 6 7
     +---------------+---------------+---------------+---------------+
   4 ! 12 Byte AEAD_IV ...                                           :
     +---------------+---------------+---------------+---------------+
   8 : ...                                                           :
     +---------------+---------------+---------------+---------------+
  12 : ...                                              ... AEAD_IV  !
     +---------------+---------------+---------------+---------------+
     : PAYLOAD X BYTES
     +---------------+---------------+---------------+---------------+
   Y : 16 Byte AEAD_ICV ...
     +---------------+---------------+---------------+---------------+
 Y+4 : ...                                                           :
     +---------------+---------------+---------------+---------------+
 Y+8 : ...                                                           :
     +---------------+---------------+---------------+---------------+
 Y+12: ...                                             ... AEAD_ICV  :
     +---------------+---------------+---------------+---------------+


all that follows is contained in the encrypted and authenticated payload

SN_FLAG = REG
    This is the payload inside the crypto container:

      0 1 2 3 4 5 6 7 0 1 2 3 4 5 6 7 0 1 2 3 4 5 6 7 0 1 2 3 4 5 6 7
     +---------------+---------------+---------------+---------------+
  16 ! Community ...                                                 :
     +---------------+---------------+---------------+---------------+
  20 : ... Community ...                                             :
     +---------------+---------------+---------------+---------------+
  24 : ... Community ...                                             :
     +---------------+---------------+---------------+---------------+
  28 : ... Community                                                 !
     +---------------+---------------+---------------+---------------+
  32 ! MAC address ...                                               :
     +---------------+---------------+---------------+---------------+
  36 : ... MAC address ...           ! IP Address ...
     +-+-+-+-+-+-+-+-+-+-+-+-+-+-+-+-+

SN_Flag = REG + ACK
    This is the payload inside the crypto container:

      0 1 2 3 4 5 6 7 0 1 2 3 4 5 6 7 0 1 2 3 4 5 6 7 0 1 2 3 4 5 6 7
     +---------------+---------------+---------------+---------------+
  16 ! Public Socket ...                                             :
     +---------------+---------------+---------------+---------------+
  20 : ... Public Socket                                             !
     +---------------+---------------+---------------+---------------+
  24 ! TODO: what else?                                              !
     +---------------+---------------+---------------+---------------+

SN_FLAG = KEEP_ALIVE

